ion-results-trump-harris-presidential-election-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheaded%20into%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20control%20of%20the%20presidency%2C%20the%20Senate%2C%20and%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20still%20one%20outstanding%20House%20race%20yet%20to%20be%20called.%20And%20its%20outcome%20could%20impact%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump's%20ability%20to%20push%20through%20his%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20California's%2013th%20Congressional%20District%20%E2%80%94%20anchored%20in%20the%20state's%20agriculture-rich%20Central%20Valley%20%E2%80%94%20former%20Democratic%20state%20Assemblyman%20Adam%20Gray%20leads%20incumbent%20GOP%20Rep.%20John%20Duarte%20by%20just%20227%20votes%20with%20an%20estimated%2099%25%20of%20the%20votes%20counted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGray%20has%20105%2C083%20votes%2C%20compared%20to%20104%2C856%20votes%20for%20Duarte%2C%20according%20to%20the%20California%20Secretary%20of%20State's%20office.%20The%20race%20is%20a%20rematch%20of%20their%202022%20contest%2C%20which%20saw%20Duarte%20ultimately%20defeat%20Gray%20by%20564%20votes%20out%20of%20nearly%20134%2C000%20ballots%20cast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20needed%20218%20seats%20to%20control%20the%20chamber%20and%20have%20already%20won%20220%20seats%2C%20while%20Democrats%20currently%20have%20214%20seats.%20So%2C%20the%20seat%20won't%20affect%20the%20balance%20of%20power.%20But%20in%20the%20narrowly%20divided%20House%2C%20the%20margins%20will%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20look%20at%20why%20this%20race%20has%20taken%20so%20long%20to%20call%20and%20why%20its%20outcome%20remains%20significant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247b2d7e1-f29d-401e-9130-1206ff600e5b%5C%22%3EBallots%20can%20arrive%20after%20Election%20Day%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20states%20won't%20count%20ballots%20that%20arrive%20after%20Election%20Day%2C%20California%20law%20allows%20ballots%20postmarked%20by%20Election%20Day%20to%20be%20counted%20if%20they%20a