20reckoning%20in%20Romania%20similar%20to%20previous%20claims%20against%20Facebook.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674c96397929f317fb4f7a02%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222814%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETikTok%20is%20facing%20accusations%20of%20election%20interference%20in%20Romania.%3Cp%3Eillustration%20by%20Roni%20Bintang%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETikTok%20is%20facing%20scrutiny%20in%20Romania%20for%20election%20interference.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERomania's%20defense%20council%20says%20TikTok's%20algorithm%20fueled%20the%20rise%20of%20a%20far-right%20candidate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETikTok%20denied%20the%20claim%20that%20it%20treated%20any%20political%20candidate's%20content%20differently%20from%20others.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20is%20facing%20accustions%20from%20regulators%20in%20Romania%20that%20content%20on%20the%20platform%20improperly%20influenced%20the%20country's%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERomania's%20Supreme%20Council%20of%20National%20Defense%20said%20in%20a%20statement%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eon%20Thursday%20that%20one%20candidate%20%26quot%3Bbenefited%20from%20massive%20exposure%20due%20to%20preferential%20treatment%26quot%3B%20from%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EC%C4%83lin%20Georgescu%2C%20a%20far-right%20populist%20and%20ally%20of%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20defeated%20leftist%20Prime%20Minister%20Marcel%20Ciolacu%2C%20the%20heavy%20favorite%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fromania-orders-election-recount-after-shock-far-right-win%2Fa-70911174%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20first%20round%20of%20presidential%20voting%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20November%2024.%20Georgescu%2C%20who%20was%20virtually%20unknown%20before%20the%20election%2C%20catapulted%20from%20obscurity%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20his%20viral%20TikTok%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20win%20secured%20Georgescu%20a%20place%20in%20a%20runoff%20vote%20scheduled%20for%20December%208.%20The%20Romanian%20Constitutional%20Court%20ordered%20a%20re-verification%20of%20the%20result%20following%20his%20surprise%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorgescu%20has%20courted%20controversy%20with%20his%20pro-Russian%20and%20anti-NATO%20rhetoric%2C%20calling%20Ukraine%20an%20%26quot%3Binvented%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20Associated%20Press.%20Romania%20borders%20Ukraine%20and%20is%20a%20NATO%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20statement%2C%20the%20Romanian%20defense%20council%20said%20there%20is%20growing%20interest%20inside%20Russia%20to%20%26quot%3Binfluence%20the%20public%20agenda%20in%20Romanian%20society%26quot%3B%20and%20disrupt%20social%20cohesion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorgescu's%20sudden%20popularity%20on%20TikTok%20appears%20to%20have%20helped%20fuel%20his%20election%20victory.%20One%20Romanian%20think%20tank%20told%20the%20AP%20that%20his%20TikTok%20following%20and%20engagement%20%E2%80%94%20his%20posts%20garnered%20over%20100%20million%20views%20in%20the%20weeks%20before%20the%20election%20%E2%80%94%20appeared%20%26quot%3Bsudden%20and%20artificial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Council%20of%20National%20Defense%20said%20TikTok%2C%20owned%20by%20the%20Chinese%20company%20ByteDance%2C%20failed%20to%20label%20the%20videos%20of%20one%20candidate%20%E2%80%94%20presumed%20to%20be%20Georgescu%20%E2%80%94%20as%20campaign%20content.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20defense%20council%20said%20that%20not%20labeling%20the%20content%20as%20campaign-related%20drastically%20increased%20its%20visibility%20on%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThus%2C%20the%20visibility%20of%20that%20candidate%20increased%20significantly%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20other%20candidates%20who%20were%20recognized%20by%20the%20TikTok%20algorithms%20as%20candidates%20for%20the%20presidential%20elections%2C%20and%20the%20content%20promoted%20by%20them%20was%20massively%20filtered%2C%20exponentially%20decreasing%20their%20visibility%20among%20platform%20users%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20accusation%20against%20TikTok%20in%20Romania%20mirrors%20similar%20claims%20against%20Facebook%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffewer-americans-visited-fake-news-sites-before-2020-election-study-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2016%20US%20presidential%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20Russia%20used%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20to%20sow%20discord%20that%20favored%20Republicans%20and%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20has%20also%20faced%20scrutiny%20in%20the%20United%20States%20for%20allowing%20political%20ads%20that%20included%20disinformation%20in%20the%20lead-up%20to%20the%202024%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20did%20not%20immediately%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20company%20told%20Politico%20that%20it%20denies%20that%20Georgescu%20was%20treated%20differently%20by%20the%20platform%20than%20other%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20categorically%20false%20to%20claim%20his%20account%20was%20treated%20differently%20to%20any%20other%20candidate%2C%26quot%3B%20spokesperson%20Paolo%20Ganino%20told%20the%20outlet.%20Ganino%20added%20that%20Georgescu%20was%20treated%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20same%20way%20as%20every%20other%20candidate%20on%20TikTok%2C%20and%20subject%20to%20exactly%20the%20same%20rules%20and%20restrictions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-election-interference-romania-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733081893000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674c95a6e45a68623a2752ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-election-interference-romania-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%