show%2F115872781.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bangladesh%20Stops%2054%20Iskcon%20Members%20From%20Crossing%20Into%20India%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBangladesh's%20immigration%20police%20on%20Sunday%20turned%20back%2054%20members%20of%20the%20International%20Society%20for%20Krishna%20Consciousness%20(Iskcon)%20who%20possessed%20valid%20travel%20documents%20and%20wanted%20to%20cross%20into%20India%20from%20the%20Benapole%20border%20checkpoint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20media%20reported%20that%20the%20Bangladesh%20police%20did%20not%20allow%20them%20to%20proceed%20citing%20%26quot%3Bsuspicious%20travel%26quot%3B.%20Some%20even%20claimed%20that%20the%20total%20number%20of%20Hindus%20arriving%20at%20the%20border%20crossing%20was%20over%2070.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20reported%20that%20the%20Hindu%20devotees%20from%20various%20parts%20of%20Bangladesh%20had%20arrived%20at%20the%20land%20port%20along%20the%20international%20border%20on%20Saturday%2C%20wanting%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20through%20the%20Benapole-Petrapole%20crossing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20consulted%20the%20Special%20Branch%20of%20Police%20and%20received%20instructions%20from%20the%20higher%20authorities%20not%20to%20permit%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Benapole%20Immigration%20Checkpost%20Officer-in-Charge%20(OC)%20Imtiaz%20Ahsanul%20Quader%20Bhuiya%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20the%20Bangladesh's%20Daily%20Star.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhuiya%20reportedly%20mentioned%20that%20the%20Bangladeshi%20authorities%20did%20not%20allow%2054%20Iskcon%20devotees%20to%20travel%20to%20India%20due%20to%20%26quot%3Bsuspicions%20regarding%20their%20travel%20purposes%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20several%20members%20of%20the%20group%20-%20who%20were%20made%20to%20wait%20at%20the%20checkpoint%20since%20Saturday%20night%20-%20stated%20that%20they%20were%20travelling%20to%20India%20for%20religious%20rituals%20with%20valid%20passports%20and%20visas%20but%20were%20still%20turned%20back%20on%20Sunday%20with%20the%20authorities%20not%20giving%20any%20clear%20reason%20for%20their%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20going%20to%20participate%20in%20a%20religious%20ceremony%20in%20India%2C%20but%20immigration%20officials%20stopped%20us%2C%20citing%20the%20absence%20of%20government%20permission%2C%26quot%3B%20Saurabh%20Tapandar%20Cheli%2C%20one%20of%20the%20Iskcon%20members%2C%20told%20local%20media%20outlets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Integrated%20Check%20Post%20(ICP)%20in%20Petrapole%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%20was%20jointly%20inaugurated%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20former%20Bangladesh%20PM%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20in%20July%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minorities%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20especially%20Hindus%2C%20have%20come%20under%20a%20severe%20attack%20by%20Islamist%20elements%20in%20Bangladesh%20after%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20interim%20government%20in%20the%20country%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Advisor%20Muhammad%20Yunus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20after%20the%20arrest%20and%20denial%20of%20bail%20to%20Chinmoy%20Krishna%20Das%20-%20a%20spokesperson%20of%20the%20Bangladesh%20Sammilit%20Sanatan%20Jagran%20Jote%20who%20is%20also%20associated%20with%20Iskcon%20Bangladesh%20-%20India%20had%20spotlighted%20that%20there%20are%20several%20documented%20cases%20of%20arson%20and%20looting%20of%20minorities'%20homes%20and%20business%20establishments%2C%20as%20well%20as%20theft%20and%20vandalism%20and%20desecration%20of%20deities%20and%20temples%2C%20reported%20from%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20unfortunate%20that%20while%20the%20perpetrators%20of%20these%20incidents%20remain%20at%20large%2C%20charges%20should%20be%20pressed%20against%20a%20religious%20leader%20presenting%20legitimate%20demands%20through%20peaceful%20gatherings.%20We%20also%20note%20with%20concern%20the%20attacks%20on%20minorities%20protesting%20peacefully%20against%20the%20arrest%20of%20Shri%20Das.%20We%20urge%20Bangladesh%20authorities%20to%20ensure%20the%20safety%20and%20security%20of%20Hindus%20and%20all%20minorities%2C%20including%20their%20right%20of%20freedom%20of%20peaceful%20assembly%20and%20expression%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20a%20statement%20issued%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20New%20Delhi%20remains%20concerned%20with%20the%20increasing%20extremist%20rhetoric%20and%20incidents%20of%20violence%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20several%20radicals%2C%20including%20Hasnat%20Abdullah%20and%20Sarjis%20Alam%20-%20who%20led%20the%20so-called%20'Anti-Discrimination%20Student%20Movement'%20that%20eventually%20resulted%20in%20the%20fall%20of%20government%20headed%20by%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20in%20August%20-%20continue%20to%20orchestrate%20a%20disinformation%20campaign%20against%20Hindus%20and%20spiritual%20organisation%20Iskcon%2C%20calling%20it%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bagent%20of%20the%20Awami%20League%26quot%3B%20that%20should%20be%20banned%20in%20the%20country%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20sending%20Chinmoy%20Krishna%20Das%20to%20jail%2C%20Bangladesh's%20Financial%20Intelligence%20Unit%20(BFIU)%20had%20ordered%20the%20freezing%20of%20his%20bank%20account%20and%20also%20of%2016%20more%20Hindus%20who%20are%20associated%20with%20Iskcon%20in%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20had%20strongly%20condemned%20the%20%26quot%3Btortures%26quot%3B%20inflicted%20on%20common%20people%20by%20the%20interim%20government%20in%20Bangladesh%20and%20called%20for%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20release%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20Hindu%20priest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20top%20leader%20of%20the%20Sanatan%20religious%20community%20has%20been%20unjustly%20arrested%2C%20he%20must%20be%20released%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hasina.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bangladesh%20Awami%20League%20(AL)%20president%20and%20daughter%20of%20the%20'Father%20of%20the%20Nation'%20Bangabandhu%20Sheikh%20Mujibur%20Rahman%20also%20spotlighted%20several%20incidents%20of%20persecution%20of%20members%20of%20minority%20communities%20that%20have%20been%20reported%20from%20across%2052%20districts%20in%20Bangladesh%20since%20her%20resignation%20on%20August%205%2C%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20temple%20has%20been%20burnt%20in%20Chittagong.%20Previously%2C%20mosques%2C%20shrines%2C%20churches%2C%20monasteries%20and%20houses%20of%20the%20Ahmadiyya%20community%20were%20attacked%2C%20vandalized%20and%20looted%20and%20set%20on%20fire.%20Religious%20freedom%20and%20security%20of%20life%20and%20property%20of%20people%20of%20all%20communities%20should%20be%20ensured%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20the%20killing%20of%20innumerable%20Awami%20League%20leaders%20and%20workers%2C%20students%20and%20members%20of%20the%20law%20and%20order%20forces%2C%20harassment%20is%20going%20on%20through%20assaults%20and%20arrests.%20I%20strongly%20condemn%20and%20protest%20against%20these%20anarchist%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20Hasina%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733070840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fm4ni96vg_iskcon-temple-istock_625x300_27_November_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbangladesh-stops-54-iskcon-members-from-crossing-into-india-7148680%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bangladesh's%20immigration%20police%20on%20Sunday%20turned%20back%2054%20members%20of%20the%20International%20Society%20for%20Krishna%20Consciousness%20(Iskcon)%20who%20possessed%20valid%20travel%20documents%20and%20wanted%20to%20cross%20into%20India%20from%20the%20Benapole%20border%20checkpoint.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%2